political philosophy that

01:22:06.294 --> 01:22:08.460
is articulated, to the
extent that it's articulated,

01:22:08.460 --> 01:22:12.150
it's that strong nations
have to be homogeneous.

01:22:12.150 --> 01:22:13.530
That there has to be--

01:22:13.530 --> 01:22:18.740
which, de facto, means a white,
you know, European culture.

01:22:18.740 --> 01:22:21.514
And so you have to strip
any part-- to be successful,

01:22:21.514 --> 01:22:22.930
to be a part of
that society-- you

01:22:22.930 --> 01:22:25.080
have to strip anything
that doesn't fit in that.

01:22:25.080 --> 01:22:27.360
How do we best counter
that narrative?

01:22:27.360 --> 01:22:29.850
How do we advance
a narrative where

01:22:29.850 --> 01:22:32.580
a pluralistic diverse society,
where there is no majority,

01:22:32.580 --> 01:22:35.987
is not threatening and is a
positive feature-- future.

01:22:35.987 --> 01:22:37.070
How do we articulate that?

01:22:37.070 --> 01:22:39.340
How do we counter
that narrative?

01:22:39.340 --> 01:22:43.090
RHONDA GONZALEZ: I would ask for
