01:25:16.530 --> 01:25:20.200
subscribes to the idea that
we have to be homogeneous.

01:25:20.200 --> 01:25:21.950
And I think that there
are a lot of people

01:25:21.950 --> 01:25:27.180
that actually want to see a
more nationalist approach.

01:25:27.180 --> 01:25:28.942
That are in fact not
even close to what

01:25:28.942 --> 01:25:30.150
you may be thinking they are.

01:25:30.150 --> 01:25:33.537
And they feel as if they've been
created into a class of bigots.

01:25:33.537 --> 01:25:35.120
I know them, because
I work with them.

01:25:35.120 --> 01:25:36.744
I know them because
they're my friends.

01:25:36.744 --> 01:25:40.460
I know them because they
voted for Obama in 2008.

01:25:40.460 --> 01:25:42.447
And they voted for
him again in 2012.

01:25:42.447 --> 01:25:44.030
And they don't exactly
see the country

01:25:44.030 --> 01:25:45.685
as having to be
homogeneous, they just

01:25:45.685 --> 01:25:47.810
view that their country
should be a country of laws

01:25:47.810 --> 01:25:49.340
where the laws are respected.

01:25:49.340 --> 01:25:52.820
And this issue of immigration
is such a delicate one.

01:25:52.820 --> 01:25:54.410
Because yes, in
fact, you can respect

01:25:54.410 --> 01:25:55.670
undocumented immigrants.

01:25:55.670 --> 01:25:58.220
You can say that the
overwhelming majority of them

01:25:58.220 --> 01:25:59.485
are wonderful human beings.

01:25:59.485 --> 01:26:01.610
And you can never speak
about them the way you did,

01:26:01.610 --> 01:26:02.660
Mr. Trump.

01:26:02.660 --> 01:26:05.450
But at the same time say,
we are a nation of laws.

01:26:05.450 --> 01:26:08.090
And there is a problem with
undocumented immigration

01:26:08.090 --> 01:26:09.080
in some places.

01:26:09.080 --> 01:26:10.970
And then you can have
that honest discussion

01:26:10.970 --> 01:26:13.910
without feeling as if the
country must look the same way.

01:26:13.910 --> 01:26:16.280
And too many people, I
think, feel as if they've

01:26:16.280 --> 01:26:18.560
been put in a class of bigots.

01:26:18.560 --> 01:26:20.446
And they're very,
very upset about it.

01:26:20.446 --> 01:26:23.070
I speak to them, and I think we
have to change the conversation

01:26:23.070 --> 01:26:24.350
and change the tone, I think.

01:26:24.350 --> 01:26:26.570
I know I'm in the minority
of people when I say that.

01:26:26.570 --> 01:26:28.605
Because if not,
there can't be unity

01:26:28.605 --> 01:26:30.980
when you have a group of people
that have been castigated

01:26:30.980 --> 01:26:32.349
as bigots when they're not.

01:26:32.349 --> 01:26:33.890
And I'm very concerned
about the idea

01:26:33.890 --> 01:26:36.110
of having a homogeneous
society when that's not

01:26:36.110 --> 01:26:39.390
in fact what so many people
that supported the Trump agenda,

01:26:39.390 --> 01:26:41.450
if you will, were behind.

01:26:41.450 --> 01:26:42.582
[INTERPOSING VOICES]

01:26:42.582 --> 01:26:44.040
AUDIENCE: If I can
respond to that.

01:26:44.040 --> 01:26:48.080
